# GitHub Repo Sync

Whenever you create or modify a file in the `uptech/business-development` or `uptech/writing` repos, **always push the changes to GitHub via the MCP immediately after** — do not leave them only on disk.

## Workflow

1. Before editing an existing file, fetch it with `get_file_contents` to get the current `sha`
2. Make your edits
3. Push with `create_or_update_file` (single file) or `push_files` (multiple files)

## Repo reference

| Repo | Owner | Branch |
|------|-------|--------|
| `business-development` | `uptech` | `main` |
| `writing` | `uptech` | `main` |

## Single file update

```
create_or_update_file:
  owner: uptech
  repo: business-development        # or writing
  branch: main
  path: deals/pipeline.md           # file path within repo
  content: <full file content>
  message: <short description of what changed>
  sha: <sha from get_file_contents>  # required for existing files
```

## Multiple files in one commit

```
push_files:
  owner: uptech
  repo: writing
  branch: main
  message: <short description>
  files:
    - path: linkedin-posts/matt/2026-03-25-slug.txt
      content: <full content>
    - path: linkedin-posts/adam/2026-03-25-slug.txt
      content: <full content>
```

## Commit message style
- Be specific: `"Update Gameday deal — MSA signed"` not `"Update pipeline"`
- For LinkedIn posts: `"Add Matt post: {topic slug}"`
